cID=8668.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Need advice on which char to use...</span><hr size=1> I have a 63 Necro and I use to solo in Sebilis and sometimes PoG whenever I needed some fast cash drops. Recently my brother quit and I now have his account and 63 Mage. He doesnt have epic but is only 1 item away from getting it. Just wanted to ask which character I should use next time I need to go to PoG or Seb for cash. I don't have the means to 2-box so its one or the other.  How do the pets compare and what would the down time be like for the mage? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bawang>Bawang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/03 7:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8668.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Need advice on which char to use...</span><hr size=1> If you've played your necro to 63 that's a lot of learning investment you've made.  A mage is so different you're going to feel uncomfortable and probably make fatal errors.  I think you should stick to your necro until you learn how to play the mage.<br>
<br>
It's not clear cut which is best.  A necro is better where crowd control is needed.  A mage is better where pure offensive power is required.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dabrixmgp>DabrixMGP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/03 8:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8668.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Need advice on which char to use...</span><hr size=1> I do have some experience with my brother's mage since I leveled him from 57-60 while he was studying abroad so its not like I just ebayed some guys uber mage and I have only been playing EQ for 2 weeks.  Just need to know how efficient the mage would be or if I should just stick with my necro.  Been wanting to toy around some with his mage anyways and see how the new Air and Water pets are comapred to mine. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artulyn1>Artulyn1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 358<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/03 8:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8668.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/armiture/eq/artulyn-tag.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Need advice on which char to use...</span><hr size=1> Yeah, the main difference between the two classes is necros can crowd control and tend to take longer to kill things. Mages are DD oriented and have few DoTs, while the necros use DoTs and have few DDs. I think once you get used to playing the 63 mage, you'll be pleased with how fast critters die.<br>
<br>
Hehehe, last night I finally dinged 61 and after my group broke up I went to Rathe Mtns to try out my new spells on the local HG population. One blast from FBoT and the giants were down to around 21% life, and my pet would finish it off in a matter of seconds after engaging it. Made like 250pp in a half hour of blasting away. <p>&lt;Crispin' Critters for Mithaniel Marr since 29MY1999&gt;<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mysite.verizon.net/res0qqnm/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/artulyn-sig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
&lt;Political Correctness is Intellectual Fascism&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dabrighter2>Dabrighter2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#333333>(2/3/03 10:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8668.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Need advice on which char to use...</span><hr size=1> There is nothing that farms greens/light blues faster that the Epic pet or the 49th Fire pet.  {Green/light blue to them}<br>
<br>
However, I think the mobs you are talking about are much higher level and will damage the pets considerably.  In this case, the mage must use his mana to either nuke the mob down faster or to heal the pet.  You will be slowed to the mages mana regeneration rate.  <br>
<br>
I suspect you Necro will solo faster, but depends on how much the mobs damage the mages pets.  Too bad you can't two box, The mage/Necro teams works very well.  The Necro snares/fears sends in pet.  The mage nukes occasionaly and sends in a backstabbing water pet.  Works very well.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tenner>tenner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(2/3/03 11:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8668.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Mages are DD oriented and have few DoTs<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
what few dot? <br>
mages has <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>TWO</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> dots and that's it, and for faming green, mage &gt; necro. <br>
And for mage Dots, it's 10 mana less than the leve dd and it takes longer to do the same damage, anyone with the right mind shouldn't use it. <br>
<br>
If you have 61 air + DS the criters die fast enough.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dabrixmgp>DabrixMGP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(2/3/03 11:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8668.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ..</span><hr size=1> Not really talking about true greens for which the epic pet would destroy while I go make a sandwich.  My two places I go to a lot for fast cash are Sebilis and PoG.  Will probably have to throw PoG out for the mage and only use necro when I go there.  The only problem I am seeing I wll have with the mage is no way to heal myself, no CC, and no real way to get back mana other than rodding. I think I will just go there and play each character a few nights solo and see what works out and which I like better. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 405<br> <font color=#333333>(2/4/03 12:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8668.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ..</span><hr size=1> For PoG I'd say Necro, for Sebilis I'd say Mage.<br>
<br>
In PoG you will be getting singles and snare/fearing them or burning them down with Neuro while LoZ tanks them. You can pact your pet to heal him and lifetap to get your mana back. (With focus you're lifetapping 1k which isn't a bad nuke at the same time.)<br>
<br>
In Sebilis you will be fighting 2-4 frogs/beetles/golems at a time and the damage shield and damage mitigation of the Air pet will make a huge difference in how fast you mow through them. Just use your pet heals and keep him DS'd. Save mana to burn down runners and you will do fine.<br>
<br>
(I have an Epic Mage and a 63 Necro.. this is what I do.)<br>
<br>
Although I'll be running the Mage in PoG pretty soon to get a new Robe. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
